761,IssuesEvent,2016-12-06 15:06:37+00:00,24005390,tBuLi/symfit,2188968,tBuLi,,,closed,Style guide vector model mistake,"[{'id': 456210594, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/tBuLi/symfit/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}]",[],0,"``` python
model = {y_1: x**2, y_2: x**3}
sol_1, sol_2 = model(x=xdata)
```

Does not work obviously. Should be:

``` python
model = Model({y_1: x**2, y_2: x**3})
sol_1, sol_2 = model(x=xdata)
```

http://symfit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/style_guide.html
",{},{}
769,IssuesEvent,2012-01-04 17:59:50+00:00,342640,byroot/pysrt,179599,ThiefMaster,,,closed,Newline between subs should be done in SubRipFile,[],[],4,"Right now the SubRipItem tests contain a trailing newline, like this:

    u'MILES:\nNo one stops us.\n'
    u'No one ever has.\n'

When changing the text you need to ensure to keep (or re-add) that trailing newline since otherwise the next sub in the file will come directly after the edited one instead of after the edited one plus one newline.

This separating newline is not really part of the subtitle itself though, so it shouldn't be there and be added automatically when saving the subtitles to a file.",{},{}
