855,IssuesEvent,2016-10-09 05:25:17+00:00,30492678,facetoe/zenpy,1366896,facetoe,,,closed,Issue with created_greater_than being ignored in zenpy.search?,[],[],3,"Loving zenpy, this has helped make a lot of sense of this to me. That said, am a bit of a noob here, and having a devil of a time figuring out what's going on. I'm trying to setup an export that'll pull all of the ticket data from the past day. 

```
yesterday = datetime.now() - timedelta(days=1)

from zenpy import Zenpy
zenpy = Zenpy(**creds)

for ticket in zenpy.search(""test"", type=""ticket"", created_greater_than=(yesterday)):
    print(ticket.id)
    id = ticket.id
    subj = ticket.subject
    created = ticket.created_at
    for comment in zenpy.tickets.comments(ticket.id):
        body = comment.body
```

This works, but it completely ignores the created_greater_than part and starts pulling every that has the string ""test""

Ideally my zenpy.search would just be 
```
for ticket in zenpy.search(created_greater_than=(yesterday)):
```
but that returns Invalid search: Please provide a valid search query which might be part of the problem. Any idea what's going wrong? I've also tried this from the documentation guide, but different error there

```
for ticket in zenpy.search(type='ticket', created_between=(yesterday, today)):
```
Returns: zenpy.lib.exception.ZenpyException: *_between requires a list!

Any idea what's going on with datetime and zenpy? 
",{},{}
