1943,IssuesEvent,2017-08-24 18:11:31+00:00,13698035,IanHarvey/bluepy,31292802,gabrielchagnon,,,closed,bluepy.btle.BTLEException: Unexpected response (rd),[],[],1,"Hello,

I am developing an IOT demo using a Thunderboard React and a Raspberry Pi3.  The latter is running my Python script that is based on the script posted by Silicon Labs for the Sensor version.

So my script is pretty much complete at this point; reading the environmental data, detect which button was pressed and having the LEDs blink according to a pattern that I specify.

The issue that I face is that a keep getting the following ""Unexpected response"" :
  File ""tbreact_scan.py"", line 97, in blinkLeds
    **tb.writeLeds**(b'\04')
  File ""/home/python/eclipse-workspace/tbreact/tbreact_v2.py"", line 202, in writeLeds
    self.char['ledState'].write(data, withResponse=True)
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/bluepy/btle.py"", line 163, in write
    return self.peripheral.writeCharacteristic(self.valHandle, val, withResponse)
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/bluepy/btle.py"", line 502, in writeCharacteristic
    return self._getResp('wr')
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/bluepy/btle.py"", line 369, in _getResp
    resp = self._waitResp(wantType + ['ntfy', 'ind'], timeout)
  File ""/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/bluepy/btle.py"", line 337, in _waitResp
    raise BTLEException(BTLEException.INTERNAL_ERROR, ""Unexpected response (%s)"" % respType)
**BTLEException**: Unexpected response (rd)

When I was using Python3 it could happen when scanner.scan(5) (line 13 in tbreact_scan.py) was invoked or when I was trying to writing to the LEDs characteristic for the purpose of establishing a blinking pattern.  Having read here that Python3 may have been the culprit I moved my development to Python2 and never again got an error during the scan phase.

Now that the functionalities required for my IOT demo are working, I am at a lost to figure why I keep getting the above error message randomly when I write to the LED characteristic.  Sometimes I get the error message within a couple of writes, sometimes it will work flawlessly minutes at a time...

The error is consistant with both my development platform Ubuntu 16.04 with Eclipse and on the Raspberry Pi (The July version of jessie; unpatched fresh install and patched via apt-get update + upgrade).  The writes to the LED characteristic are spaced by 0.3 second so I do not believe that I am pushing too hard from my side to the Thunderboard.  It is possible that I am not doing my write correctly but I currently doubt this as Python has been relentless in checking the stuff that I thought that was correct!!

I have attached my current source.  For readability, feel free to delete the the debugging stuff (dbg) as I was (and still is) for my own education on what a BTLE device sends.

Thanks in advance for any insight,

Gabriel

[tbreact.zip](https://github.com/IanHarvey/bluepy/files/1247210/tbreact.zip)



",{},{}
