2094,IssuesEvent,2018-02-23 08:52:21+00:00,23076316,horazont/aioxmpp,271710,horazont,,,closed,Do not allow forwarding of application stanzas until resource binding has completed,"[{'id': 122716547, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/horazont/aioxmpp/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"Currently, when an application enqueues a stanza before the stream has first been established, the stanza is sent *before* the resource binding takes place. This can lead to all sorts of funny issues:

* messages will be lost or errored back
* IQ requests will fail with not-authorized
* presence may be errored back or be lost

… much of this (except IQs) happens without the application being the wiser.

The stream should not accept stanzas from services or application code until it has been fully negotiated.",{},{}
