3823,IssuesEvent,2015-04-30 00:01:23+00:00,1014759,autocracy/python-ipy,1471533,ktims,,,opened,No way to force printing of host prefix lengths,[],[],0,"Current string conversion functions don't distinguish between the default (print prefix only for non-host entities) and user-specified wantprefixlen values. The code in _printPrefix conflates None with 1, and always applies the default setting even when wantprefixlen is set. There is an instance variable to override this, but this is not very conducive to efficient scripting (this is not even exposed in the constructor for IP), and IMO breaks the expectation of 'wantprefixlen'.

In my opinion, I expect 'wantprefixlen' set to non-zero to always print the prefix length regardless of what the value is.

A pull request is incoming.",{},{}
