5924,IssuesEvent,2015-07-27 03:47:43+00:00,38095954,eternnoir/pyTelegramBotAPI,1109538,eternnoir,,,opened,Let client support next_step_handler to handle message which user replay.,[],[],0,"We let bot handle command like '/search google'. It easy to implement by pyTelegramBotAPI. 
But if we want split this command to '/search','google' two step. Not that simple now.

 So I want to create new method like `register_for_new_message`. Use them like this:

```python
def process_step1(message):
    if message.text == 'No':
        bot.reply_to(message, ""Good bye!"")
    else:
        message = bot.send_message(chat_id, ""Go to step2?"", )
        bot.register_for_new_message(sent_message, process_step2)

def process_step2(message):
    if message.text == 'No':
        bot.reply_to(message, ""Good bye!"")
    else:
        message = bot.send_message(chat_id, ""Go to step3?"", )
        bot.register_for_new_message(sent_message, process_step3)

def process_step3(message):
