5959,IssuesEvent,2016-12-21 02:32:01+00:00,8186469,isislovecruft/python-gnupg,907241,isislovecruft,,,closed,decrypt does not work with gpg 2.1.9 without '--pinentry-mode loopback',"[{'id': 28336300, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/isislovecruft/python-gnupg/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'isislovecruft', 'id': 907241, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/907241?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/isislovecruft', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/isislovecruft/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"Decrypt (`decrypt()`) does not work for me unless passphrase has been previously passed to gpg2.

I'm using:

python-gnupg version 2.0.2
gpg (GnuPG) 2.1.9

My use case is relatively simple:

```
...     g.decrypt(f.read(), passphrase=passphrase, output=decfile)
```

If I trace it with strace, I see ""Inappropriate ioctl for device <Pinentry>"" message.

```
$ strace -fqq -s512 <command>
[pid  3645] <... read resumed> ""ERR 83918950 Inappropriate ioctl for device <Pinentry>\n"", 1002) = 55
```

I was able to make it work by:
- Enabling `gpg-agent` to run with `allow-loopback-pinentry`, and 

```
$ grep allow-loopback-pinentry ~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf 
allow-loopback-pinentry
```
- Adding `--pinentry-mode loopback` as an additional parameter to gnupg. I added it under `GPGBase._make_args()` and tested that decryption works.

Can `--pinentry-mode loopback` be added to gnupg?
",{},{}
