6033,IssuesEvent,2017-05-01 18:38:20+00:00,22954701,noirbizarre/flask-restplus,5684118,beverku,,,opened,Defining self referential nested Fields,[],[],0,"Is there a way to define self-referential nested fields?  The following snippet results in a RecursionError:
```python
todo = api.model('Todo', {
    'id': fields.Integer(readOnly=True, description='The task unique identifier'),
    'task': fields.String(required=True, description='The task details'),
    'sub-todos': fields.List(fields.Nested('Todo'))  # This dosen't work
})
```

I am able to achieve most of what I want using the following, but it seems there should be a less awkward way of defining this, as it's a pretty common use case.

```python
todo = api.model('Todo', {
    'id': fields.Integer(readOnly=True, description='The task unique identifier'),
    'task': fields.String(required=True, description='The task details'),
})

todo2 = api.inherit('Todo2', todo, {
    'sub-todos': fields.List(fields.Nested(todo))
})
```",{},{}
