6994,IssuesEvent,2018-04-30 23:04:08+00:00,34864402,apache/incubator-mxnet,2778341,anirudhacharya,47359,apache,opened,Support for LpPooling in Pooling operator,[],[],0,"[Pooling operator](http://mxnet.incubator.apache.org/api/python/ndarray/ndarray.html#mxnet.ndarray.Pooling) currently supports ‘avg’, ‘max’ and ‘sum’ pooling. There is no support for lp pooling. 

LpPooling is computed by calculating the Lp norm on all values of a subset of the input tensor according to the kernel size and then down-sampling the data into the output tensor.  Pytorch and Caffe2 have support for this operator.

The existing Pooling operator should be modified to support Lp pooling.

@piiswrong @szha @zheng-da @haojin2 @eric-haibin-lin ",{},{}
