7833,IssuesEvent,2015-11-01 23:49:29+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,1027979,erikbern,251374,spotify,closed,Composition of parameters,[],[],14,"Consider this small example:

```python
class A(Task):
    log = Parameter(default=""/var/log.txt"")

class B(Task):
    logPath = Parameter(default=""~/"")

class C(A, B):
    logFile = Parameter(default=""log.txt"")
```

Now, I want to tell task ``C`` to overwrite its inherited ``log`` parameter, which should be ``os.path.join(logPath, logFile)``. To be consistent with the instance caching, I cannot use the
``__init__`` method. However, I could extend the default ``get_param_values`` method, but
that does not seem clean enough to me. In cases like this I would propose something like a
hook to ensure parameter flexibility when e.g. working in such inheritance scenarios. If ``A.log``
had not default (which might be the case if you want to define ``A`` as some kind of interface),
the extension of ``get_param_values`` wouldn't work anyway.

Edit: solved in PR #1254.",{},{}
7836,IssuesEvent,2015-10-22 19:47:46+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,7432199,dlstadther,251374,spotify,opened,Python 2.7.10 Boto S3 Issue,[],[],0,"With the introduction and Python 2.7.9 (and 2.7.10), Boto s3 cannot handle bucket names with . (periods) in them.

This issue has a long-running thread [here](https://github.com/boto/boto/issues/2836).

I can confirm that luigi.S3 worked with buckets containing periods for Python 2.7.6. However, it does not work with 2.7.10 (my current python installation).

It may be worth looking into how to implement the fix noted by mattse for US buckets into Luigi.s3

        if '.' in bucketName:
            conn = S3Connection(awsAccessKeyID, awsSecretKey, calling_format=OrdinaryCallingFormat())
        else:
            conn = S3Connection(awsAccessKeyID, awsSecretKey)


Alternatively, we may want to switch luigi.S3 towards boto3 as it seems to be the upcoming boto replacement.",{},{}
