7942,IssuesEvent,2017-03-30 19:58:15+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,2323156,kimkulling,265533,assimp,closed,instance_image in collada 1.5 files exported from c4d,[],[],0,"Hi,

it seems cinema exporter was using this attribute to export textures, instead of <source> (as done in version 1.4). This error was showing when trying to load this kind of files:

Expected start of <source> element.

I'm attaching a patch with some changes, avoiding this behaviour when format 1.5 is detected.

Best regards,
Sergio

patch:
diff -r 038eda279259 code/ColladaParser.cpp
--- a/code/ColladaParser.cpp    Wed Feb 05 16:57:34 2014 +0100
+++ b/code/ColladaParser.cpp    Fri Feb 07 18:00:59 2014 +0100
@@ -1446,7 +1446,7 @@
                // don't care for remaining stuff
                SkipElement( ""surface"");
            } 
-           else if( IsElement( ""sampler2D""))
- ```
        else if( IsElement( ""sampler2D"") && FV_1_4_n == mFormat )
      {
          // surface ID is given inside <source> tags
          TestOpening( ""source"");
  ```
  
  @@ -1457,6 +1457,17 @@
  
  ```
          // don't care for remaining stuff
          SkipElement( ""sampler2D"");
  ```
-           }
-           else if( IsElement( ""sampler2D"") && FV_1_5_n == mFormat )
-           {
-               // surface ID is given inside <instance_image> tags
-               TestOpening( ""instance_image"");
-               int attrURL = GetAttribute(""url"");
-               const char \* url = mReader->getAttributeValue( attrURL);
-               url = url+1;
-               pParam.mType = Param_Sampler;
-               pParam.mReference = url;
-               SkipElement( ""sampler2D"");
          } else
          {
              // ignore unknown element
",{},{}
