8006,IssuesEvent,2018-01-26 14:55:13+00:00,744916,gem/oq-engine,2463856,micheles,316546,gem,closed,Add a command/utility to dump a single calculation,"[{'id': 262430947, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gem/oq-engine/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '009800', 'default': True}, {'id': 230695424, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/gem/oq-engine/labels/proposal', 'name': 'proposal', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}]",[],0,"`oq dump` is already able to dump the entire `oqdata`, we should add the ability to dump a single calculation.

Probably, as suggested by @micheles, it's enough just to recreate a record n the destination db having the hdf5 (which contains all the needed info). In this case only the import phase needs to be changed.

In this way it's possible to run a calculation on a foreign machine and then use such calculation with a local engine server instance.

Suggested by @klunk386 ",{},{}
