8754,IssuesEvent,2018-03-28 14:58:00+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,17437250,lgh2,647025,pypa,opened,UnicodeDecodeError when long_description is a file in a different encoding,[],[],0,"I was doing some testing the other day, and tried using a file in ISO/IEC 8859 encoding as the `long_description`.  I got the following error message: 

```
File ""setup.py"", line 9, in <module>
    long_description = f.read()
  File ""/home/user/Python/Readme_GFM/venv/lib/python3.6/codecs.py"", line 698, in read
    return self.reader.read(size)
  File ""/home/user/Python/Readme_GFM/venv/lib/python3.6/codecs.py"", line 501, in read
    newchars, decodedbytes = self.decode(data, self.errors)
UnicodeDecodeError: 'utf-8' codec can't decode byte 0xc2 in position 0: invalid continuation byte
```
I did a little research, and found that a fix for this was submitted [here](https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/pull/537/files), but it seems that the fix was removed [here](https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/pull/802/files#diff-81de4a30a55fcc3fb944f8387ea9ec94).  I'm not certain why it was removed.

My understanding is that [UTF-8 is the only text encoding supported in package metadata](https://packaging.python.org/specifications/core-metadata/?highlight=encoding#description-content-type-optional), but I may be wrong about this, especially since setuptools still has to support Python 2. 

I think that trapping the error and letting users know that their file is not in UTF-8 would be helpful. I'm happy to submit a patch for this, if you would like. 
",{},{}
8763,IssuesEvent,2017-05-10 14:06:00+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,681260,giampaolo,647025,pypa,opened,WARNINGS: imp module is deprecated,[],[],0,"I get this every time I install a package by using `python -Wa setup.py install`. In order to reproduce it pyc files must be deleted first.

