9175,IssuesEvent,2016-02-11 11:32:19+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,6603890,ujjwal-researcher,897180,scikit-image,opened,Automatic inversion of binary image stored as TIFFILE. ,[],[],0,"Summary of Issue : A binary image stored as an uncompressed TIFF file is automatically inverted upon invoking `skimage.io.imread()` The issue immediately evaporates when the TIFF file is converted to a JPEG File.

## Experiment - 1 (With a Binary image stored as a TIFF File). 

**NOTE** : The file has been taken from an independent location and has not been read or re-written. The issue is the same across any other TIFF image I have tried.
```
from skimage import io
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = io.imread('mask.tif')
io.imshow(img)
plt.show()
```
## Experiment - 2 (With the same Binary image converted to JPEG).

```
from skimage import io
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = io.imread('mask.jpg')
io.imshow(img)
plt.show()
```

**NOTE** : The conversion was done by `convert img.tif img.jpg`

To reproduce the issue : 

- Go to https://goo.gl/rvYQOa and download  img.tif and img.jpg

- Run the codes corresponding to the above experiments ",{},{}
