9635,IssuesEvent,2016-01-28 19:58:30+00:00,24642075,sunscrapers/djoser,2290727,tooreht,1218240,sunscrapers,opened,Logout after password change,[],[],0,"As of django >= 1.7 setting a new password has the following new behaviour (From [Django source] (https://github.com/django/django/blob/1.8.8/django/contrib/auth/views.py#L304)):

```python
# Updating the password logs out all other sessions for the user
# except the current one if
# django.contrib.auth.middleware.SessionAuthenticationMiddleware
# is enabled.
update_session_auth_hash(request, form.user)
```

It would be nice to adapt the code to address this issue. Maybe a new setting `LOGOUT_ON_PASSWORD_CHANGE ` would make sense to make use of this new behaviour.

Here some similar projects which already handle this:

- [django-rest-auth](https://github.com/Tivix/django-rest-auth/blob/master/rest_auth/serializers.py#L258)
- [django-user-accounts](https://github.com/PersonalGenomesOrg/django-user-accounts/blob/8d43830ace662802d5071454b701fe96a94e9903/account/views.py#L472)",{},{}
9677,IssuesEvent,2016-10-04 11:15:03+00:00,5407062,kivy/pyjnius,22613831,yasiha,1266152,kivy,opened,jnius.detach() not safe with  local variables,[],[],0,"Sorry, my English is not good, Can only give examples：

ByteBuffer = autoclass('java.nio.ByteBuffer')
Thread(target = runthread).start()
def runthread():
    try:
        dst = ByteBuffer.allocate(20)
        .....
    finnaly:
        jnius.detach()

The program crashes when exiting the thread, Unless we do things like this

def runthread():
    dst = None
    try:
        dst = ByteBuffer.allocate(20)
        .....
    finnaly:
        if dst: del dst             #dealloc in current jnienv
        jnius.detach()

so why not give us  jnius.thread


I hope someone can understand what I said",{},{}
