10234,IssuesEvent,2015-01-30 16:11:11+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,6180405,Tryten,1505683,FortAwesome,opened,file icon suggestion,[],[],0,"I modify the font-awesome.css in the following way and I figured I would make the suggestion for future releases.  It allows me to programmatically assign icons to file links by just using the file extension (i.e.: $class = '.fa-file-' . $filetype . '-o'). (I do the same thing for archive types (zip, tr, gz, etc) and a few other file types that I work with.

.fa-file-word-o:before,
.fa-file-doc-o:before,
.fa-file-docx-o:before {
  content: ""\f1c2"";
}
.fa-file-excel-o:before,
.fa-file-xls-o:before,
.fa-file-xlsx-o:before {
  content: ""\f1c3"";
}
.fa-file-powerpoint-o:before,
.fa-file-ppt-o:before,
.fa-file-pptx-o:before {
  content: ""\f1c4"";
}
.fa-file-photo-o:before,
.fa-file-picture-o:before,
.fa-file-image-o:before,
.fa-file-bmp-o:before,
.fa-file-gif-o:before,
.fa-file-jpeg-o:before,
.fa-file-jpg-o:before,
.fa-file-png-o:before {
  content: ""\f1c5"";
}",{},{}
