10731,IssuesEvent,2018-03-09 18:12:20+00:00,15510254,openfisca/openfisca-core,1175927,benjello,1794404,openfisca,opened,Question: how is input_to_period_tuple supposed to be used ?,[],[],0,"Hi there!

I really enjoy OpenFisca, but I recently encountered an issue.

### Here is what I did:
```
print periods.Period(periods.input_to_period_tuple(""2014-04-01:4"")) 
```
### Here is what I expected to happen:
Obtain a period object
```
month:2014-04:4
```
### Here is what actually happened:
```
/home/benjello/openfisca/openfisca-core/openfisca_core/periods.pyc in __str__(self)
    318         """"""
    319 
--> 320         unit, start_instant, size = self
    321         if unit == ETERNITY:
    322             return 'ETERNITY'

ValueError: need more than 2 values to unpack
```
The error may come from the fact that a period cannot be initialized with 
```periods.input_to_period_tuple(""2014-04-01:4"")``` 
since it returns 
```
((u'month', (2014, 4), 4), None)
```
Notice the absence of Instant

## Context

I was updating the following [notebook](https://github.com/openfisca/tutorial/blob/master/notebooks/how_to_handle_periods.ipynb) 

I identify more as a:

- Developer _(I create tools that use the existing OpenFisca code)_.
",{},{}
10733,IssuesEvent,2017-08-22 15:41:19+00:00,15510254,openfisca/openfisca-core,222463,MattiSG,1794404,openfisca,opened,Add a `/entities` endpoint to the API,[],[],0,"Returns a JSON object where the property names is the `key` property of the entity and where the value is an Object with the following properties:

- String `plural`. Mandatory.
- String `documentation`, coming from the entity docstring. Defaults to `""""`.
- Object `roles` if the entity is not a person (in case the entity is a person, `roles` must be falsy), where the name is the `key` property and where the value is an object with the following properties:
  - String `plural`. Mandatory.
  - Boolean `mandatory`. Defaults to `false`.
  - Number `max` (if one is defined).

`subroles` are not to be exposed yet.",{},{}
10747,IssuesEvent,2018-01-16 14:30:09+00:00,15510233,openfisca/openfisca-france,25476945,monbocal,1794404,openfisca,opened,Vérifier la formule de calcul de l'ASI/ASPA pour un couple ,[],[],0,"Suite à un retour utilisateur, j'ai regardé la formule de calcul de l'ASI/ASPA. Je me demande si toutes les ressources sont bien prises en compte, par exemple l'AAH.

Le lien vers la formule : https://legislation.openfisca.fr/asi_aspa_base_ressources_individu
```
    # Inclus l'AAH si conjoint non éligible ASPA, retraite et pension invalidité
    aah = individu('aah', three_previous_months, options = [ADD])
    aah = aah * not_(aspa_eligibilite) * not_(asi_eligibilite) * not_(pension_invalidite)
```

Les documents sur service-public laissent penser que l'AAH est cependant prise en compte tout le temps : https://www.service-public.fr/particuliers/vosdroits/F16940 et https://www.service-public.fr/particuliers/vosdroits/F16871 .

