10923,IssuesEvent,2018-03-07 17:58:39+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,31542053,ggrieco-tob,2314423,trailofbits,closed,EVM: STOP instruction returns random values,"[{'id': 536968928, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 723733286, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/ethereum', 'name': 'ethereum', 'color': 'e27af4', 'default': False}, {'id': 851821712, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/trailofbits/manticore/labels/priority-high', 'name': 'priority-high', 'color': 'f71dec', 'default': False}]",[],1,"### Manticore version
f4118f4f0f0db9ebcb97c08b103b04224bc795ee

### Summary of the problem
The STOP instruction returns an array of random values instead of 0

### Step to reproduce the behavior
```
# contract.sol
pragma solidity ^0.4.20;

contract Test{
    function () payable{
        assembly{
            stop
        }
    }
}
```

$ manticore contract.sol
m.main:INFO: Beginning analysis
m.ethereum:INFO: Starting symbolic transaction: 1
