11058,IssuesEvent,2018-01-18 12:19:56+00:00,58705171,opencobra/memote,8027271,ChristianLieven,2708410,opencobra,opened,Improve error reporting in memote,[],[],0,"#### Problem description
Some helper functions graciously catch errors to return an output that is then represented by tests as 'passed'. While raised errors and their error messages are available to users of the command line tool, users that only rely on the report will not see error messages.

Errors that are raised in helper functions should not terminate the report generation, but instead their messages/codes should be reported and displayed.",{},{}
11090,IssuesEvent,2016-02-05 09:15:25+00:00,24213271,adobe-type-tools/afdko,1527880,brawer,2768660,adobe-type-tools,opened,[spec] Syntax of ignore sub statement is incomplete,[],[],0,"In [section 5.f.ii of the OpenType Feature File specification](http://www.adobe.com/devnet/opentype/afdko/topic_feature_file_syntax.html#5.f.ii), the syntax of the `ignore sub` statement is currently defined like this:
```
ignore substitute <backtrack glyph sequence>*
            <marked glyph sequence>
            <lookahead glyph sequence>*;
```

However, later down in example 3, the statement then gets illustrated with an example that does not conform to this syntax:
```
ignore substitute @LETTER a' n' d', a' n' d' @LETTER;
```

Also, makeotf seems to accept a comma-separated list of backtrack/input/lookahead triples. Therefore, the syntax specification for the `ignore sub` statement should be changed to reflect reality.",{},{}
