11737,IssuesEvent,2016-11-04 13:19:07+00:00,15381974,groveco/django-sql-explorer,3911074,spapas,3093407,groveco,opened,Schema preview should respect EXPLORER_CONNECTION_NAME ,[],[],0,"Hello,

the schema preview is always using the ""default"" SQL connection while it should use the setting defined in EXPLORER_CONNECTION_NAME instead. 

I know that the reason for this is to use a read only connection for EXPLORER_CONNECTION_NAME which is the same as the default connection, however after some tests it seems that the django-sql-explorer works great with a totally different connection than the default as the EXPLORER_CONNECTION_NAME. So, what I did is that I used the default connection for the the users and django stuff of django-sql-explorer and added a second connection to a totally different database which I run queries on.

This actually is related to issue #115, however fixing this issue (respect EXPLORER_CONNECTION_NAME  for schema preview) should be much easier.",{},{}
