12101,IssuesEvent,2018-01-05 17:47:14+00:00,14991049,nccgroup/Scout2,13443216,vvkdby,4067082,nccgroup,reopened,Cross Account Assume Role Access support missing in Scout2,"[{'id': 69447324, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nccgroup/Scout2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],5,"I can setup my AWS EC2 instance with the role that has the permissions to assume any role it wants, as described in [this post](https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/iam-assume-role-cli/). Specifically, if I have a policy like the following:
```
{
    ""Version"": ""2012-10-17"",
    ""Statement"": [
        {
            ""Effect"": ""Allow"",
            ""Action"": [
                ""sts:AssumeRole""
            ],
            ""Resource"": ""*""
        }
    ]
}
```
I can run aws cli commands with just the role_arn and external_id. But I cannot run Scout2 with a profile containing just the role_arn and external_id, since it requires the presence of `aws_secret_access_key` and `aws_access_key_id`. Some shallow surfing of the source code tells me that [this line seems to be the problem](https://github.com/nccgroup/Scout2/blob/master/AWSScout2/__main__.py#L56). ( [This line also seems related](https://github.com/nccgroup/opinel/blob/master/opinel/utils/credentials.py#L451) )

Scout2 should have similar behavior as aws cli in this case, i.e. it should be okay without `aws_secret_access_key`.",{},{}
