12524,IssuesEvent,2016-06-17 17:58:03+00:00,3791384,coursera-dl/coursera-dl,7540399,rishabhgpt,5588942,coursera-dl,closed,html file name length problem with windows,[],[],3,"🚨Please review the [Troubleshooting](../#troubleshooting) section
before reporting any issue. Don't forget to check also the current issues to
avoid duplicates.

### Subject of the issue
While downloading html file of enormous length like:
installing-octave-matlab-on-mac-os-x-10-10-yosemite-and-10-9-mavericks-and-later.html
windows doesn't allows to create file and download stops with No such file or directory exception
### Your environment
* Operating System (name/version): Windows 7, Pro
* Python version: 2.7
* coursera-dl version:

### Steps to reproduce
Try downloading Andrew Ng's ML class 
* Is the problem happening with the latest version of the script? yes
* Do you have all the recommended versions of the modules? See them in the
