12541,IssuesEvent,2018-06-06 19:53:28+00:00,91020334,ni/nimi-python,11483903,texasaggie97,5598284,ni,closed,"Documentation tip for repeated capabilities is confusing at best, wrong at worst","[{'id': 656403760, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NTY0MDM3NjA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ni/nimi-python/labels/docs', 'name': 'docs', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 763891646, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3NjM4OTE2NDY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ni/nimi-python/labels/priority-medium', 'name': 'priority-medium', 'color': 'ed1cc6', 'default': False}]",[],1,"In our generated documentation, any method that has a repeated capability includes [the same blurb](https://github.com/ni/nimi-python/blob/master/build/helper/documentation_snippets.py#L4):

```
This method requires repeated capabilities (usually channels). If called directly on the
nidmm.Session object, then the method will use all repeated capabilities in the session.
You can specify a subset of repeated capabilities using the Python index notation on an
nidmm.Session instance, and calling this method on the result.
```

This is great. Except since #718 we have ""containers"". Even for channels, we are supposed to use the channel container: `session.channels[2].my_property`.

Given this:

* The blurb is incorrect. We should encourage the use of the container.
* Can we fix the blurb to refer to the appropriate container as appropriate? This may require additional metadata.
```
",{},{}
