12947,IssuesEvent,2018-02-11 16:07:09+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,824194,pipermerriam,6250754,ethereum,opened,Create generic transaction execution abstraction,"[{'id': 631592722, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ethereum/py-evm/labels/Good%20First%20Issue', 'name': 'Good First Issue', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}]",[],0,"### What is wrong?

Currently, there is a lot of code duplication in the `execute_transaction` functions.

- [Frontier](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/9df7a3d02bc8a1a2d898d010c63ab7d567950d19/evm/vm/forks/frontier/vm_state.py#L45-L185)
- [Sharding](https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/sharding/evm/vm/forks/sharding/vm_state.py#L49-L184)

### How can it be fixed

A basic abstraction for the `execute_transaction` functionality. 

The functions are currently divided into 3 distinct logical sections.  It would be pretty straight forward to create a class which implements hooks for each of these sections.

```python
class BaseTransactionExecution:
    def __call__(self, vm_state, transaction):
        message = self.run_pre_computation(vm_state, transaction)
        computation = self.run_computation(vm_state, message)
        return self.run_post_computation(vm_state, computation)

    def run_pre_computation(vm_state, transaction):
        raise NotImplementedError(...)

    def self.run_computation(vm_state, message):
        raise NotImplementedError(...)

    def run_post_computation(vm_state, computation):
        raise NotImplementedError(...)
```
",{},{}
