13025,IssuesEvent,2016-06-29 23:32:59+00:00,8566509,delph-in/pydelphin,1428419,goodmami,6363662,delph-in,opened,Fix how entity/type info is accessed in UDX derivations,[],[],0,"UDX can now be interpreted as allowing grammar type annotations on all nonterminal nodes, not just preterminals. The `delphin.derivation.Derivation` class works well with this information, but the accessors are named `entity()` (for the full entity+type concatenated name), `basic_entity()` for just the entity portion, and `lexical_type()` for just the grammar type. These are no longer appropriate, since the type need not be a lexical type.

Maybe we can just have `entity()` and `type()` and decompose by default. This would follow the JSON format more closely, at least.",{},{}
