Before updating Conda:

```
conda:       4.0.8-py27_0 --> 4.1.1-py27_0 
conda-env:   2.4.5-py27_0 --> 2.5.0-py27_0 
```

The command:

```
source activate py35
```

was working fine in my Z shell.  Now with Conda 4.1.1 I get this error:

```
prepending /homes/trembl/miniconda2/envs/py35/bin to PATH
/homes/trembl/miniconda2/bin/activate:export:59: not valid in this context: $PR_CYAN$PR_ULCORNER$PR_HBAR$PR_GREY(\
```

---

ISR: I have tested this with Conda 4.1.1 and zsh on OS X 10.11.5 (using Homebrew-installed zsh) and it sort of works OK for me (I am not keen on the double round brackets, nor on the fact that Conda has made its own decision regarding what my prompt should look like:

```
➜  ~ source activate ana40py35
prepending /Users/ijstokes/anaconda/envs/ana40py35/bin to PATH
((ana40py35)) ijstokes@petawawa:~% 
```
