      ""size_in_bytes"": 63
    },
...
```

From what I've seen in the conda-build source this seems to be the [expected behavior](https://github.com/conda/conda-build/blob/9395a482df893ec6966226c257ab91c2840f47c2/conda_build/build.py#L522-L523) for `noarch_python` packages.  

The example package is available in the [jjhelmus_testing channel](https://anaconda.org/jjhelmus_testing/imagesize/files).

This package was created with conda build 2.1.1 using the following recipe:

``` yaml 
package:
  name: imagesize
  version: 0.7.1

source:
  fn: imagesize-0.7.1.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/i/imagesize/imagesize-0.7.1.tar.gz
  sha256: 0ab2c62b87987e3252f89d30b7cedbec12a01af9274af9ffa48108f2c13c6062

build:
  number: 99
  noarch_python: True
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
```",{},{}
