13251,IssuesEvent,2016-12-29 12:40:45+00:00,12024604,OpenCobolIDE/OpenCobolIDE,1681217,ColinDuquesnoy,6609701,OpenCobolIDE,closed,Go to Assignments sometimes uses a complete wrong identifier,"[{'id': 51529254, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/OpenCobolIDE/OpenCobolIDE/labels/Bug', 'name': 'Bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': False}]",[],0,"## Description

I've seen this multiple times in a sample source I can not provide.

The source contains the following parts:

```cobol
[...]
78 CODE-GET-TABLE-NAME  value '123'.
[...]
PERFORM GET-TABLE-NAME
[...]
GET-TABLE-NAME SECTION.
```

When using F7 on `GET-TABLE-NAME` in the `PERFORM` statement the view switches up to `CODE-GET-TABLE-NAME`, not down to the section with the same name.

This happens with multiple sections.

### System information

- Operating System: Windows
