13254,IssuesEvent,2016-10-03 18:47:30+00:00,26839425,arista-eosplus/pyeapi,1184465,dathelen,6643264,arista-eosplus,closed,test_api_interfaces.TestApiVxlanInterface fails on DUTs running 4.15 and higher,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/arista-eosplus/pyeapi/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]","[{'login': 'dathelen', 'id': 1184465, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1184465?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/dathelen', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dathelen/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"If you run the suite of system tests on a DUT running EOS version 4.15.0 or higher the test_get in the TestApiVxlanInterface class fails:

```
FAIL: test_get (test_api_interfaces.TestApiVxlanInterface)
Traceback (most recent call last):
File ""/Users/dt/eosplus/pyeapi/test/system/test_api_interfaces.py"", line 343, in test_get
self.assertEqual(result['multicast_group'], '')
AssertionError: 'decap' != ''
```

This is due to a new EOS command with the following syntax:
`[no] vxlan multicast-group decap`

Therefore the current regex in `_parse_multicast_group` will match on decap when it tries to parse through show running-config all interface vxlan.  The resolution to this issue will be to update the regex in `_parse_multicast_group` to match on a correctly formatted IPv4 multicast group.",{},{}
