13482,IssuesEvent,2017-11-10 19:49:18+00:00,94585736,Azure/service-fabric-cli,26749906,samedder,6844498,Azure,opened,Invalid or incorrect application packages will result in 500 errors during `application upgrade`,[],[],0,"If there's a mistake in my application package, such as invalid parameter names, or changes in settings that are not allowed, `sfctl application upgrade` responds with a 500 error message. This is counter-intuitive since a 400 error message is expected when clients send invalid requests or invalid application packages.

