13896,IssuesEvent,2016-02-08 00:21:34+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,2482408,michaelpacer,7388996,jupyter,opened,"Rename ""cut cell"" and other shortcuts to take selections into account",[],[],0,"Currently the shortcut name for cutting a selection of cells is ""cut cell"". I imagine this stemmed from when multicell selection wasn't possible, but now when I selected something and then saw the cut cell action name, I hesitated to do this with selection not knowing if it would apply to only the cursor cell or the entire selection.

