13908,IssuesEvent,2016-04-15 18:01:05+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,2096628,blink1073,7388996,jupyter,opened,Update Session to take an arbitrary name?,[],[],0,"We talked today at the JupyterLab meeting about how the Session would map to a source code file or a console.  We could just set the `notebook:path` to be a file path or a console session name, but it would be be generic to have a session id take this interface:

```typescript
interface ISessionId {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  kernel: {
      name: string;
      id: string;
  }
}
```",{},{}
13937,IssuesEvent,2017-07-19 16:33:19+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,192614,jasongrout,7388996,jupyter,opened,Output area height is rounded when fixing height on clear,[],[],0,"In https://github.com/jupyter/notebook/blob/5192d72c63369d7167c5472d06f87072d68ecc53/notebook/static/notebook/js/outputarea.js#L969, we use jquery to find and fix the height of an output area in order to prevent jumpiness when clearing an output area. However, this function rounds the height to the nearest integer, which causes some jitter. It would be better would be to use `.getBoundingClientRects().height`, which doesn't round the height.
",{},{}
