14506,IssuesEvent,2017-12-17 17:19:09+00:00,23953531,androguard/androguard,431045,reox,8758456,androguard,opened,Is there a better implementation for MUTF-8 Strings?,"[{'id': 692172229, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/androguard/androguard/labels/DEX%20Parser', 'name': 'DEX Parser', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 128903816, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/androguard/androguard/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 128903817, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/androguard/androguard/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}, {'id': 781196112, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/androguard/androguard/labels/low%20hanging%20fruits', 'name': 'low hanging fruits', 'color': '36a1aa', 'default': False}]",[],0,"This is the current implementation: https://github.com/androguard/androguard/blob/aa18f723c115c902cb495476a178eb1f9c0ec014/androguard/core/bytecodes/dvm.py#L1800-L1847

We would like to read the Strings from the DEX file and have them in a useful format - i.e. unicode?

I read in the documentation of Android, that the good thing about MUTF-8 is, that the strings will be always null terminated! This means, we can simply get the null terminated string from the dex file and parse it later!
I found this implementation: https://github.com/google/enjarify/blob/master/enjarify/mutf8.py
Maybe we should stick to that one?",{},{}
