14532,IssuesEvent,2018-05-22 18:18:51+00:00,34739117,pytest-dev/pluggy,291685,tgoodlet,8897583,pytest-dev,opened,Allow for user specified key/values in marks?,"[{'id': 939136981, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytest-dev/pluggy/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': '139699', 'default': False}, {'id': 205263668, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytest-dev/pluggy/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]",[],0,"Pertaining to the original request in #133 does it make sense to allow users to pass in custom key/val pairs to marks (via `**kwargs` or some other API) such that user defined collection and/or hook calling behaviour can be controlled/modified by the user based on their own inputs (maybe it's more relatable in the context of #151).

