14663,IssuesEvent,2016-05-21 18:38:11+00:00,26784827,dotnet/core,481297,Yuioup,9141961,dotnet,opened,Instructions for CentOS should use ~/bin,[],[],0,"The instructions on https://www.microsoft.com/net/core#centos say:

```bash
curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/cli/rel/1.0.0-preview1/scripts/obtain/dotnet-install.sh | bash /dev/stdin --version 1.0.0-preview1-002702 --install-dir ~/dotnet
sudo ln -s ~/dotnet/dotnet /usr/local/bin
```

In My Humble Opinion, I think it is not wise to link a global `/usr/local/bin` to point to an executable in a user's home directory. This can cause problems on a multi-user system.

I think the instructions should be:

```bash
curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/cli/rel/1.0.0-preview1/scripts/obtain/dotnet-install.sh | bash /dev/stdin --version 1.0.0-preview1-002702 --install-dir ~/dotnet
mkdir -p ~/bin
sudo ln -s ~/dotnet/dotnet ~/bin
```",{},{}
