15559,IssuesEvent,2016-06-16 14:51:15+00:00,33120392,zalando-stups/senza,107613,rafaelcaricio,11431876,zalando-stups,opened,Add flag to expose error instead of writing it to a file,[],[],0,"Would be nice to have a option to explicitly tell Senza to show the unknown exception stack trance in the console instead of writing it to a file.

### Current behaviour

It shows this message:
```
Unknown Error.
  Please create an issue with the content of /var/folders/90/pz80sxl93gl11zjsbmylwmxj42vx03/T/senza-traceback-_bv0iaac
```

### Expected behaviour
In case of calling Senza with something like `senza create broken.yaml --stacktrace-visible` then it would simply display the whole stack trace of the error in the console.

### Why?

It is important for tools like Lizzy that call Senza commands in background be able to pipe the actual errors that are happing while running Senza to the logs.",{},{}
