15911,IssuesEvent,2018-02-01 02:43:10+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,836375,rgbkrk,12401040,nteract,closed,Three kinds of AppRecords,[],[],1,"Right now our `AppRecord` is basically tied to Electron. @captainsafia and I did some talking about this ~1 week ago (?) and we think we've got three different kinds of `AppRecord`s, some of which have overlap and some of which do not.

## Current `AppRecord`

```
type AppRecordProps = {
  // All Apps
  executionState: ""not connected"" | ""busy"" | ""idle"" | ""starting"",
  channels: ?Channels,
  notificationSystem: ?Object,
  // All apps... maybe (?)
  kernelSpecName: ?string,
  kernelSpecDisplayName: ?string,
  kernelSpec: ?Object,
  isSaving: boolean,
  lastSaved: ?Date,

  // is this the github token?
  token: ?string,

  // electron specific
  spawn: ?ChildProcess,
  connectionFile: ?string,

  // currently only electron
  configLastSaved: ?Date,
  // is this key used (?)
  error: any
};
```

## `JupyterAppRecord`

Some of the above

* token
* channels
* kernel id
* session id

Intended for `nteract_on_jupyter`

## `BinderAppRecord`

Taking cues from `play`, we will need to manage both [server entities](https://github.com/nteract/nteract/blob/d4d3ca37b1732f894addcbae165c94c51a79414f/applications/play/redux/PLAN.txt#L29) and kernel entities. On a classic notebook app, we only need one server and kernel.

Intended for `notebook-on-next`, maybe `play` (since they're similar)




  ",{},{}
