15937,IssuesEvent,2018-07-05 07:50:42+00:00,36358216,angr/cle,19667060,canpadawan,12520807,angr,opened,ELFTLSObject lies about its size,[],[],0,"When ELFTLSObject has to be rebased in Loader._map_object, it computes size of object with 
```python
obj_size = obj.max_addr - obj.min_addr
```
then the clemory is [mapped](https://github.com/angr/cle/blob/master/cle/loader.py#L708) but the clemory max_addr is bigger that obj.max_addr, so if you try to rebase another object right after this one this would fail.

That fix seem to work for me but I haven't tested it much
```diff
diff --git a/cle/backends/tls/elf_tls.py b/cle/backends/tls/elf_tls.py
index 680d965..c973a75 100644
--- a/cle/backends/tls/elf_tls.py
+++ b/cle/backends/tls/elf_tls.py
@@ -119,7 +119,7 @@ class ELFTLSObject(TLSObject):
 
     @property
     def max_addr(self):
-        return self.mapped_base + TLS_TOTAL_HEAD_SIZE + self.max_data + 2*self.arch.bytes + 2*self.arch.bytes*self.max_modules
+        return self.mapped_base+self.memory.max_addr
 
     def get_addr(self, module_id, offset):
         """"""
```
",{},{}
15970,IssuesEvent,2017-04-10 20:36:01+00:00,40328394,angr/angr,759365,axt,12520807,angr,opened,Question about SimActions for SimProcedures,[],[],0,"@ltfish , @zardus :

When I create a SimProcedure, the generated action list will not contain any kind of TMP actions, as it does for VEX lifted code (if TRACK_TMP_ACTIONS is enabled). 

For example it generates these actions for an empty simprocedure:
```
<SimActionData <simproc>() reg/read>    # read value of esp
<SimActionData <simproc>() reg/write>   # esp += 4
<SimActionData <simproc>() mem/read>    # read ret addr from stack
<SimActionExit <simproc>() conditional> # this should be 'default' i guess, but doesnt matter too much for now
<SimActionData <simproc>() reg/write>   # set eip to the value read from stack
```
My problem is that for example the DDG analysis is depending on the tmp actions, which are missing from this list, so it can't really handle these list of actions. 

I want to create an analyis what is relying on SimActions (like DDG does).
 
What is the original purpose of SimActions?
Is it encouraged to base an analysis on them?
If yes, how can I overcome the situation above?",{},{}
