16240,IssuesEvent,2016-09-13 14:12:02+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,opened,Organisation of tests,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],0,"I have come across a potential bug in the sorting of the tests and I'd like some clarification.

I think we had decided that all unit and integration tests requiring an external resource such as DIRAC or LCG should be marked as external and _not_ run as part of the continual testing but only run nightly.

If we're sticking to this I'm going to tag some tests as external which haven't been marked as such but if we've changed our minds on this what is the policy with regard to tests requiring access to external resources?",{},{}
16292,IssuesEvent,2015-10-13 10:43:35+00:00,31315021,Kinto/kinto,67073,ametaireau,13413813,Kinto,opened,WebPush integration,[],[],0,"[WebPush](http://www.w3.org/TR/push-api/) allows client to pass along an URL that will trigger a push notification on their side.

Supporting WebPush allows to notify User-Agents that *something* happens. I see a few things to investigate further:

- Fine-grained notifications: clients should tell when notifications should be sent their way. For instance, they might only be interested in updates to data they created.
- Permissions (related to the first point). We shouldn't notify people that don't have access to the information, otherwise we might leak some data.",{},{}
