16459,IssuesEvent,2018-04-13 11:02:41+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,189031,orgicus,14095512,IntelRealSense,opened,macOS Installation issues,[],[],0,"----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Required Info                         |                                                                |
|---------------------------------|------------------------------------------- |
| Camera Model                       | { D415 | D435 } | 
| Firmware Version                   | D415: 05.09.02.00 | D435: 05.08.14.00) | 
| Operating System & Version |   MacOS 10.11.6  | 
| Platform                                 | Macbook Pro  |
| SDK Version                            |  { 2.10.3 }                          | 


### macOS Installation issues

I ran into multiple issues simply following the [macOS installation doc](https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/blob/master/doc/installation_osx.md):

```bash
	Undefined symbols for architecture x86_64:
	  ""librealsense::make_less_screamy(char const*)"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::get_string(rs2_rs400_visual_preset) in rs_advanced_mode.cpp.o
	  ""_libusb_error_name"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::platform::libuvc_backend::query_usb_devices() const in libuvc.cpp.o
	      librealsense::platform::libuvc_uvc_device::get_data_usb(uvc_req_code, int, int) const in libuvc.cpp.o
	      librealsense::platform::libuvc_uvc_device::set_data_usb(uvc_req_code, int, int, int) const in libuvc.cpp.o
	      librealsense::platform::uvclib_usb_device::uvclib_usb_device(librealsense::platform::usb_device_info const&) in libuvc.cpp.o
	      librealsense::platform::uvclib_usb_device::foreach_usb_device(libusb_context*, std::__1::function<void (librealsense::platform::usb_device_info const&, libusb_device*)>) in libuvc.cpp.o
	      librealsense::platform::uvclib_usb_device::send_receive(std::__1::vector<unsigned char, std::__1::allocator<unsigned char> > const&, int, bool) in libuvc.cpp.o
	  ""_libusb_get_device_speed"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::platform::get_usb_descriptors(libusb_device*) in libuvc.cpp.o
	  ""_libusb_get_parent"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::platform::uvclib_usb_device::foreach_usb_device(libusb_context*, std::__1::function<void (librealsense::platform::usb_device_info const&, libusb_device*)>) in libuvc.cpp.o
	  ""_libusb_get_port_numbers"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::platform::get_usb_descriptors(libusb_device*) in libuvc.cpp.o
	  ""_libusb_handle_events_completed"", referenced from:
	      _uvc_handle_events(void*) in init.cpp.o
	      void* std::__1::__thread_proxy<std::__1::tuple<uvc_start_handler_thread(uvc_context*)::$_0> >(void*) in init.cpp.o
	ld: symbol(s) not found for architecture x86_64
	```

I already had libusb and libuvc installed on my system so the fix was to set `USE_SYSTEM_LIBUSB = OFF`

which left me with only one error to deal with:

```bash
	Undefined symbols for architecture x86_64:
	  ""librealsense::make_less_screamy(char const*)"", referenced from:
	      librealsense::get_string(rs2_rs400_visual_preset) in rs_advanced_mode.cpp.o
	ld: symbol(s) not found for architecture x86_64
	clang: error: linker command failed with exit code 1 (use -v to see invocation)
	make[2]: *** [librealsense2.2.10.3.dylib] Error 1
	make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/realsense2.dir/all] Error 2
	make: *** [all] Error 2
```

...for which I just used a very hacky workaround:

```c++
	#define STRCASE(T, X) case RS2_##T##_##X: {\
        static std::string s##T##_##X##_str = (#X);\
        return s##T##_##X##_str.c_str(); }
    ``` in `src/ds5/advanced_mode/rs_advanced_mode.cpp`

Please let me know:

1. What's the (clean) recommended way of dealing with the `make_less_screamy` error
2. What's the best way of contributing to save others from this trouble (e.g. update [documentation](https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/blob/master/doc/installation_osx.md), [Q&A](https://github.com/IntelRealSense/librealsense/wiki/Troubleshooting-Q&A) or submit a pull request) ?

Thank you,
George
",{},{}
