16602,IssuesEvent,2017-09-28 18:32:20+00:00,43628779,python-constraint/python-constraint,7455433,evancox10,14961635,python-constraint,opened,Python 3 Incompatibility (?),[],[],0,"On lines 691-692 of __init__.py in the minConflicts.getSolution(...) method, you have the following:

lst = domains.keys()
random.shuffle(lst)

The call to random.shuffle() fails on python 3, because in python3 the dictionary .keys() method returns a set, which can't be indexed. So lst must be converted from this set into a list:

lst = list(domains.keys())
random.shuffle(lst)


Not sure how you would write the code to be compatible in both Python2 and Python3
",{},{}
