16885,IssuesEvent,2018-02-01 16:48:18+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,closed,otThreadGetDeviceRole returns OT_DEVICE_ROLE_CHILD long after the router has timed it out,"[{'id': 355043116, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'jwhui', 'id': 16142208, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/16142208?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jwhui', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jwhui/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"Hi, my team has encountered a peculiar bug which is reproduced in non-standard way, so I expect some grain of salt when looking at it. There's a setup with NCP (border) router and few (2-4) devices, all of which are custom platform. Some devices are connected to a debugger and may be paused for indefinite amount of time. If the pause is long enough that the router times-out the device, it does not reconnect once resumed. Capturing the packets show that the device only sends data requests (and receives ACKs to them). Calling otThreadGetDeviceRole always return OT_DEVICE_ROLE_CHILD, instead of OT_DEVICE_ROLE_DETACHED.
Has anyone noticed similar behavior? Could it be enough that the ACKs to data requests are enough to keep the child from switching to detached state? I have not yet looked deep enough to determine what's the exact problem here, it may as well be platform or debug related, but any suggestions on where to look first in openthread stack are welcome.",{},{}
16889,IssuesEvent,2018-05-25 17:16:34+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,closed,multicast communication with Group ID supporting,"[{'id': 355043116, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openthread/openthread/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': True}]",[],7,"Hello,
Does openthread support multicast communication like ZigBee?  
It needs a 16-bit network address called multicast address(Group ID).
Multicast: This is a transmission to every device in a particular PAN belonging to a dynamically defined multicast group, and within a given transmission radius measured in hops.

Thank you.
",{},{}
