17439,IssuesEvent,2017-03-28 22:53:04+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,1499652,chrissound,17889013,certbot,opened,Command line arguments not working correctly in 0.12 but does in 0.9.3,[],[],0,"```
sudo docker run --rm -v $pwd/dataStatic/nginx/:/var/www/html/public/ -it certbot/certbot ""certonly --webroot -w /var/www/example/ -d www.example.com -d example.com -w /var/www/other -d other.example.net -d another.other.example.net""
usage: 
  certbot [SUBCOMMAND] [options] [-d DOMAIN] [-d DOMAIN] ...

Certbot can obtain and install HTTPS/TLS/SSL certificates.  By default,
it will attempt to use a webserver both for obtaining and installing the
cert. 
