17471,IssuesEvent,2017-04-21 01:18:39+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,220205,jsha,17889013,certbot,opened,"Unwrap ""max retries exceeded"" errors",[],[],0,"When there is some sort of network problem, or the server is unavailable, we get an error like:

> An unexpected error occurred: ConnectionError: HTTPSConnectionPool(host='acme-v01.api.letsencrypt.org', port=443): Max retries exceeded with url: /directory (Caused by NewConnectionError('<requests.packages.urllib3.connection.VerifiedHTTPSConnection object at 0x7f020eee70d0>: Failed to establish a new connection: [Errno -2] Name or service not known',))

This is confusing because it emphasizes the ""retries"" part, when the important part is the ""Name or service not known"" part. We should handle this type of error specially and just show the actual error, not the part about exceeding retries.",{},{}
17472,IssuesEvent,2017-01-11 02:01:48+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6504915,bmw,17889013,certbot,opened,Document lineages in our user guide,"[{'id': 245387015, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}, {'id': 261409142, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/renewal', 'name': 'renewal', 'color': 'bfe5bf', 'default': False}]",[],0,"We used this concept a lot when developing Certbot and it's often a useful abstraction for thinking about certificates. We've never properly explained this term, however, so we can't really use it in our documentation.

We may or may not want to explain how lineages work to the average user, but at the very least they should be documented somewhere.",{},{}
