17647,IssuesEvent,2018-02-09 20:25:27+00:00,56792799,mozilla-releng/scriptworker,826343,escapewindow,19614164,mozilla-releng,opened,add `cache_dir` with purge request support,[],[],0,"Per Callek in IRC: we could poll https://docs.taskcluster.net/reference/core/purge-cache/references/api#open-purge-requests-for-a-provisionerid-workertype-pair between tasks. If we define a `cache_dir`, we could nuke+recreate if a purge request is set.

This should be optional, because many scriptworker instance types don't use a long-lived cache.",{},{}
17658,IssuesEvent,2018-07-23 16:20:51+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,55078,ulope,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Define default contract addresses per network-id,"[{'id': 974626989, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NzQ2MjY5ODk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': '683faf', 'default': False}, {'id': 473052337, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NzMwNTIzMzc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/usability', 'name': 'usability', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],0,"## Problem Definition

We currently only ship with one set of contract addresses. This already isn't very useful when running with anything but Ropsten.

When we start to ship a mainnet release we need to provide the defaults per network id (which we already have a command line parameter).

For networks we don't know about we should print an error message asking the user to explicitly specify the contract addresses (either on the CLI or in the / a config file).",{},{}
17677,IssuesEvent,2017-09-15 08:48:48+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Switch channel implementation to one global contract per token,"[{'id': 568592923, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/smart_contract', 'name': 'smart_contract', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"## Problem Definition

At the moment whenever we open a channel we create a smart contract per channel. We went with this implementation for simplicity reasons in the beginning but it is not optimal as it increases gas costs for channel opening due to the `CREATE` operation.

## Solution

Have a global contract managing all channels per token.


## Tasklist

- [ ] Replace the `NettingChannelLibrary` and `NettingChannelContract` with an equivalent contract managing all channels for a token.
- [ ] Make adjustments to the code so that it works with the new contracts.
- [ ] Add a changelog entry.",{},{}
17705,IssuesEvent,2017-04-03 16:02:30+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Ensure user has enough ether left in the account to safely interact with the netting channel,[],[],0,"## Problem Definition

If a uniformed user creates a netting channel with all it's ether then she will not be able to close/updateTransfer/settle it to recover it's asset.

## Solution

This is a hard problem and would required monitoring of the account's balance, an initial solution should ensure during the netting channel creation that the account's balance is sufficient to complete the close/updateTransfer + settle operations.

## Tasklist

Preliminary list of tasks (split into multiple issues)

- [ ] Add a configuration variable for the minimum number of pending transfer
- [ ] Ensure the account will has enough balance to call close/updateTransfer + the minimum pending transfer unlocks + settle",{},{}
