17752,IssuesEvent,2017-02-16 18:21:04+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,"Automatic to_host and from_host of _input, _depends, and _output","[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'BoPeng', 'id': 9889312, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9889312?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/BoPeng', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"This looks like a logical thing to do and would make the interface a bit simpler. The `from_host` is needed for the particular example because we would like to retrieve more than only the `chrName.txt`, but the whole index.",{},{}
17758,IssuesEvent,2017-02-13 16:04:02+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Better interaction with remote running jobs,"[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Say we started a remote job and the local job gets killed. When we re-running the local job, it will connect the remote server and found that it cannot create the job (failed to get a lock because the job is running) and fails.

It would be better if we can recognize the running jobs and wait for it to complete.",{},{}
17761,IssuesEvent,2017-03-08 05:06:47+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Stop after submitting one task,"[{'id': 325435541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Usually if one job fails all jobs would fail for the same reason, and if one job runs all jobs would run. We can use the`-n` (dryrun mode) option to print instead of run scripts, but it would be nice to

1. dryrun only one task because it is likely that one task is enough to see if the script is correct.
2. run only one task to check if it actually runs correct before submitting the rest of the tasks to the cluster

We could quit or prompt the user if he would like to continue to dryrun or run the rest of the job.

Not sure what this option could be named though. Perhaps `-p` (pause)?",{},{}
17764,IssuesEvent,2017-10-05 13:49:08+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,closed,Remote task copy error,[],[],3,"This uses the same MWE as #820 . Only this time I added `-r` because it is too much data to sync:

```
sos run ~/Dropbox/1.sos -q midway2 -r midway2

```
And I get these error (this is `-v2` output but `-v4` is not any more informative):
```
INFO: Executing default_1: 
