17967,IssuesEvent,2017-05-26 09:57:56+00:00,66363927,zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient,8939758,andy-maier,21196715,zhmcclient,closed,async methods with wait_for_completion=True return empty dict,"[{'id': 429586731, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/area:%20docs', 'name': 'area: docs', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 429588767, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/resolution:%20fixed', 'name': 'resolution: fixed', 'color': 'cccccc', 'default': False}, {'id': 429587708, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/type:%20bug', 'name': 'type: bug', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'andy-maier', 'id': 8939758, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/8939758?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/andy-maier', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"### Actual behavior

The asynchronous operation methods `Partition.start()` and `Partition.stop()` are documented to return `None` when called with `wait_for_completion=True`.

However, they return an empty dictionary (of type `OrderedDict`) in that case.

This possibly also happens for other asynchronous operation methods, ut has not been investigated at this point.

### Expected behavior

These methods should return `None`, as documented.

### Execution environment

* zhmcclient version: 0.12.1.dev3
* Operating system (type+version): RHEL 7.2
* HMC version: 2.13.1
* CPC version: 2.13.1",{},{}
17971,IssuesEvent,2017-05-10 07:11:49+00:00,66363927,zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient,19662677,leopoldjuergen,21196715,zhmcclient,closed,Client-side filtering does not support regexp matching,"[{'id': 429586299, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/area:%20code', 'name': 'area: code', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}, {'id': 439501531, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/discussion%20needed', 'name': 'discussion needed', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}, {'id': 429588767, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/resolution:%20fixed', 'name': 'resolution: fixed', 'color': 'cccccc', 'default': False}, {'id': 429587708, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/type:%20bug', 'name': 'type: bug', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'andy-maier', 'id': 8939758, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/8939758?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/andy-maier', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/andy-maier/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"The description in section ""Filtering"" states that match values for properties of non-enum String types are applied using regexp matching.

That is only true for those properties that can be matched on the server. The remaining properties that are being matched on the client side, are matched with exact string comparison,despite the description.

Options:
1. Leave the code as is, and adjust the documentation to account for that. The documentation would need to point out the different behavior of client-side matching and server-side matching for non-enum strings.
2. Add Python regexp matching to the code so that it is consistent with the documentation. A small update to the documentation would nevertheless be needed, in order to point out that the properties handles on the server side use Java regexp syntax, while the properties handled on the client side use Python regexp syntax (they are mostly the same, but I'm sure there are some differences).
   There is likely a difficulty in having the client-side matching distinguish enum strings from non-enum strings (the zhmcclient code is not aware of the properties of the resources, except for a few cases such as name, and uri), so we may end up using regexp matching for all properties that have a Python string type, i.e. not distinguish between enum strings and non-enum strings.

Need to discuss which option to implement.",{},{}
17976,IssuesEvent,2016-09-08 18:21:09+00:00,66363927,zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient,8939758,andy-maier,21196715,zhmcclient,opened,get_connected_vnics() returns NICs as URIs,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/zhmcclient/python-zhmcclient/labels/area:%20code', 'name': 'area: code', 'color': '207de5'}]",[],0,"`VirtualSwitch.get_connected_vnics()` returns the NICs that are connected to the virtual switch.
The current design returns these NICs with their URIs. This is inconsistent to other list functions that return resources as their corresponding Python object (`Nic` in this case).

Proposal: Return the connected NICs as a list of `Nic` objects that have just their `object-uri` property set.",{},{}
