18000,IssuesEvent,2018-07-31 20:28:37+00:00,72477752,pulumi/pulumi,3953235,joeduffy,21992475,pulumi,opened,Order of pulumi new args could be improved,"[{'id': 472686212, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NzI2ODYyMTI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pulumi/pulumi/labels/area/cli', 'name': 'area/cli', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 749222651, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3NDkyMjI2NTE=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pulumi/pulumi/labels/customer/feedback', 'name': 'customer/feedback', 'color': '7f61a1', 'default': False}, {'id': 472686249, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NzI2ODYyNDk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pulumi/pulumi/labels/kind/enhancement', 'name': 'kind/enhancement', 'color': 'E8CAAF', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'justinvp', 'id': 710598, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDU5OA==', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/710598?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/justinvp', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/justinvp/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"We got feedback about the `pulumi new` command and, after looking at the sequence of steps that led to this feedback, it occurs to me that the ordering of arguments, etc. is a bit off from what one might expect. The user who reported this tried `pulumi new <project-name>` which, to be honest, is a very reasonable assumption (probably more so than assuming `pulumi new <template>`, which is what we do today). In fact, we later added the `--dir` flag, but it's not at all evident, and is probably what most users will want to do anyway (all of our examples are slowly switching to using it).

A better flow would probably be to

* Use `pulumi new <project-name>`, instead of `pulumi new <template>`
* By default, prompt for the template, as we do today
* Support a `--template` flag for selecting the template if you know it in advance
* Behave as though `--dir <project-name>` were passed by default; if you want the current behavior of running in the current working directory -- probably rare -- you can just do `--dir .`",{},{}
