18167,IssuesEvent,2017-10-05 21:17:04+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,635088,philiprenich,22243823,streamlink,opened,Installation failing on Ubuntu 16.04,[],[],0,"
### Checklist

- [x] This is a bug report.

### Description

I am trying to install on an oDroid headless system running Ubuntu 16.04. Initially I tried using `sudo pip install streamlink` as shown in the Readme of this repo. That claimed to work, but when trying to load a Twitch stream or YouTube video, I would get the error `pkg_resources.UnknownExtra: requests 2.9.1 has no such extra feature 'socks'`

After seeing specific Ubuntu installation instructions on this page https://streamlink.github.io/install.html I removed streamlink with `pip` and followed the `apt` instructions instead. New repository added and updated, _check_. When running `sudo apt install streamlink` I received an error about unmet dependencies: `streamlink : Depends: python-streamlink (= 0.8.1-1~webupd8~xenial0) but it is not going to be installed` So I tried to install that and got the same issue for `python-cryptodomex`, and stepping down to install that said there was no installation candidate.

I feel like I may be missing an unexplained step or dependancy that is not installed on my system that is expected.

### Expected / Actual behavior

Apt install to just work (naive?)


### Environment details

Operating system and version: Ubuntu 16.04.1 LTS
Streamlink and Python version: No streamlink, Python 2.7.12",{},{}
