18425,IssuesEvent,2018-01-20 16:38:58+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,701625,Nikratio,26335827,python-trio,opened,Provide nursery.wait(),[],[],0,"I wish there was a way to wait until all tasks of a nursery have completed without leaving the nursery context manager. Background is this code:

```
async def run_server(sock, context):
    '''Run server until signal is received'''

    async with trio.open_nursery() as nursery:
        nursery.start_soon(accept_loop, nursery, sock, context)

        # Wow. In curio, this is a lot more concise:
        #await curio.SignalEvent(signal.SIGTERM, signal.SIGINT).wait()
        async with trio.catch_signals({signal.SIGTERM, signal.SIGINT}) as signal_iter:
            async for _ in signal_iter:
                _ # pyflakes bug workaround
                break

        # Signal worker tasks to terminate
        context.terminate = True

        # Stop starting new workers. It would be nice if we could
        # instead cancel just the accept_loop (without children)
        sock.shutdown(socket.SHUT_RDWR)
        sock.close()

        # Give workers time to terminate on their own.
        with trio.move_on_after(TIMEOUT):
             await nursery.join() # if only this existed 

        # Cancel any remaining workers
        nursery.cancel_scope.cancel()
``` 

I see no easy way to implement this without a `nursery.join()` method - or maybe I'm missing something?",{},{}
18428,IssuesEvent,2018-01-16 11:25:38+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,440661,lilydjwg,26335827,python-trio,closed,using a nursery without a context manager?,[],[],2,"I'm writing a class that will spawn tasks during its lifetime. I'd like to have a `self._nursery` so that I can spawn tasks and let it run (e.g. a heartbeat task). But it seems that the nursery can only be used in a context manager, so it closes in the same scope it gets created. I don't want to pass in a nursery from outside because it's an implementation detail.

How should I write such a thing, which has background tasks during its lifetime?",{},{}
