- Python Distribution and Version: 3.7.0
- Java Distribution and Version: 10.0.2
- Jep Version: 3.8.2 (latest master as of 19 August 2018, d1c7f1479ae46893fdab45c34088e1d788609b09)
- Python packages used (e.g. numpy, pandas, tensorflow): None

I have the following Python code in my project:

```Java
package org.wkh.arete;

import jep.Jep;
import jep.JepException;

public class JepTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws JepException {
        try(Jep jep = new Jep()) {
            jep.eval(""print('hello world from jep')"");
        }
    }
}
```

When I run this code, I get the following stack trace:

```
Exception in thread ""main"" jep.JepException: <class 'ImportError'>: dynamic module does not define module export function (PyInit_jep)
	at <string>.<module>(<string>:1)
	at jep.Jep.eval(Native Method)
