	at jep.Jep.<init>(Jep.java:140)
	at org.wkh.arete.JepTest.main(JepTest.java:8)
```

I may have done something wrong, because to even get to this I had to manually copy files from `site-packages/jep` to my JDK bin directory. Before doing that, I got an error saying jep was not in the `java.library.path`.

When you Google that exception message, what comes back is errors where someone mixes up Python 2 and Python 3. I don't have Python 2 installed on this machine so I'm not sure if that's what's somehow happening here.

Any ideas on what I should try? Thanks!",{},{}
