18508,IssuesEvent,2017-07-25 21:11:20+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,5989971,MatheusVellone,28732122,localstack,opened,Data persistence not working with pip installation and --docker flag,[],[],0,"I installed localstack with `pip install`.
After that, I added `export DATA_DIR=/tmp/localstack/data` env var as the docs says to my `.bashrc` file and tested with the command `echo $DATA_DIR` which gave me the correct path.
Then I started it with the `--docker` flag, created some dynamo tables (and checked their existance) and stopped localstack process.
Re-started the process with the same command and lost all tables I previously created. I've tested this a couple of times and all of them resulted in the lost of data.

To try something else, I cloned this repo and `make install` and `make infra` on it to run a local copy. At this point, the `DATA_DIR` variable already was set.
After the process was running, created the same tables, stopped process and started it again and all tables had persisted.

Shouldn't data persistance through pip installation with --docker flag work too ?",{},{}
