18561,IssuesEvent,2017-08-10 15:59:59+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,1778160,valgur,29057552,sentinelsat,opened,--footprints parameter,[],[],0,"## Question
**Should we change the `--footprints` parameter's behavior to also include the name of the file that will be created?**

Let's make it a poll. I encourage anyone to leave a thumbs up or down to voice your opinion. Comments are welcome too, of course.

## Reasoning
I've been thinking that the `--footprints` flag would be more useful if it also took the name/path of the file to be created instead of always writing it to `search_footprints.geojson`.

An example use case might be:
```
sentinelsat -g germany_aoi.geojson --sentinel 1 --footprints s1_germany_footprints.geojson
```
On the other hand, forcing the user to always provide the destination filename is a minor inconvenience as well (which we could mitigate a bit by automatically appending the `.geojson` suffix if it is missing).

Since I rarely use the `--footprints` feature myself (I rely on the Python API) and the choice is not obvious, I would like to hear everyone else's take on this.",{},{}
